##"Wartime Control" in Shiyan: SELF-HELP FOR 50 volunteers and 5,000 residents

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

The volunteers meet every day to discuss problems at work. For example, some people have suggested that e-commerce platforms try not to deliver food in the evening so that residents can have access to all kinds of food ordered as soon as possible. In view of the incomplete user name and telephone number on the order form, some people have proposed to communicate with e-commerce platforms, get them to give us the full story. After two or three conversations, the problem was really solved.

Volunteers serve and deliver food to residents

Fu Ziyang, Liang Jingyi, Beijing News

Editor | slide show proofread | Lucie

The text is about 5,010 words long and takes about 10 minutes to read

On February 15, sleet broke out and the wind blew hard in Shiyan, Hubei Province. "The weather has changed today, " Xiao Ankang, 26, said on Wechat, holding his mobile phone in front of a window. "Let young volunteers deliver food more often. "

Xiao Ankang is a resident of Guorui Lanshan county community in Zhangwan district, Shiyan province, and a member of the owner volunteer team. Since the beginning of February, he has been distributing vegetables bought online to residents of the gated community every day.

On February 12, Shiyan issued an emergency notice for Zhangwan District to impose wartime controls across the country, drawing attention to the city, which lies in the northwestern province of Hubei and borders Hubei, Henan and Shaanxi provinces. In accordance with the requirements of the new Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Shiyan epidemic prevention and control headquarters, from 2400 hours on the same day, "wartime control" will be implemented throughout the region, with a 14-day cycle. Based on the effectiveness of the city and Zhangwan District epidemic prevention and control, early release or continuing control.

According to Guan Jun, head of the Lanshan county community in Zhangwan district, as early as January 24, Shiyan closed the road into and out of the city. Two days later, the Lanshan county community also began to close. Since then, the community has set up a team of nearly 50 residents volunteers, every day for the community to register health information, food delivery for residents, at the gate guard. With them, the daily lives of thousands of families and nearly 5,000 residents can function. After "wartime control" , the volunteers' task was even more onerous.

"wartime-controlled" neighborhood

At 12:00 noon on February 15, Xiao Ankang, who was preparing to go home for dinner, received another bus of food from his fellow volunteers on Wechat. He rang the bell in room 3101 at the 10th floor, unit 1. "Hello, please come down and get your food. "

On the evening of February 12, the new Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District new pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Command (hereinafter referred to as "Zhangwan District Command") issued an emergency notice on the implementation of wartime control in the Zhangwan region (hereinafter referred to as "wartime control notice") , listing out a total of eight articles, of particular concern is Article 3: All buildings shall be completely closed to all management, except those who are fighting the epidemic and protecting the people's livelihood, and residents shall not be allowed to enter or leave; materials necessary for daily life shall be distributed or purchased on behalf of the people.

Xiao Ankang and others live in Guorui Lanshan county community in Zhangwan District. Guan Jun, the community leader, said there were 14 buildings in the complex, most of them 33 storeys and five on the first floor, and that the glass doors outside each building were locked after the wartime control notice came into effect.

Within the prescribed time of each morning and evening, medical and nursing personnel, medical and material practitioners, civil servants engaged in the fight against epidemic diseases, as well as workers engaged in basic livelihood protection such as water, electricity, oil and gas, communication networks, grain and vegetables (hereinafter referred to as "the four categories of personnel") , you can come and go with a red pass, and no one is allowed in or out without special circumstances. "volunteers guard the door to check documents, check one, let one through, " Guan said.

Volunteers stand guard at the gate of the community

Ordinary residents'daily needs are basically solved by the wechat small program in several nearby supermarkets. They can buy vegetables, daily necessities, a complete range of vegetables, even raincoats, cling film and other small items can be bought. After the supermarket delivers the goods to the community, the female volunteers are responsible for sorting, making phone calls to inform the residents. The male volunteers take the goods to the downstairs of each building with a handcart, ring the doorbell in turn, and ask the residents to go downstairs to get them. "To avoid cross-infection, we always send one home and press another, " Xiao said.

Yu Ping, 50, lives in building 5 and is a retired employee and volunteer at Dongfeng Motor Group. After closing the building, she took the phone book provided by the Neighborhood Committee, called all the owners of building 5 one by one, plus Wechat, but also pulled up a building wechat group. Residents report their health status on wechat groups every day, and Yu Ping collects information and reports it to the community. She doesn't know how to use a computer. She writes with a pen and a pad. "The community said they were going to create an APP in a couple of days so people could fill it out on their phones, so it wouldn't be too much trouble. "

After the closure of the building, Yu Ping found that two families live alone in the building, one of them also had a kidney transplant operation, they will not use the mobile phone to buy food. Yu Ping ran to knock on the door, standing at the door and the elderly to discuss buying food, buy daily necessities. Because volunteers can go in and out of the building, Yu Ping decided to go to the supermarket for the elderly, pharmacy procurement, "I left the phone to them, can find me at any time. "

The community closed to recruit volunteers

On January 24, the Chinese New Year, Shiyan began to close roads and stop public transport. Two days later, the city's new pneumonia prevention and control headquarters issued notice No. 14, requiring the owners of all small areas to "minimize access, no special reasons (for medical treatment, important posts, etc.) shall not be in and out. ".

Since January 24, Guan Jun and a grid worker have been busy, managing two neighborhoods, including Guorui Lanshan County, with a combined population of 7,000 to 8,000.

Guan Jun's work is very complicated, to register residents'health records, check the return of Wuhan personnel, to home for the residents with infants and young children to buy milk powder, to the elderly can not shop online to send vegetables, medicine. "One day at the most, I delivered food to 20 families, and at night I had to call the families who came back from Wuhan. "

On January 26, the overburdened Guan Army began recruiting volunteers through the Wechat Group of the owners' Committee, hoping for help in buying food, delivering food and checking residents' body temperatures. "Only seven or eight were recruited at first. ". However, over the next few days, more and more residents joined the ranks of volunteers. On February 5, more than 20 people, "Now, with the active party members who have gone down to serve the grassroots, there are over 40 volunteers, " Guan said.

Bao Qinyong, 44, became a volunteer on January 27. He was a civil servant in the Organization Department of the Bay Area Committee and had lived in Blue Mountains county for more than a year. He was a registered volunteer in Zhangwan District before the new crown pneumonia outbreak. "When there's a major outbreak, we just rush right up to it. It's normal. "

Yu Ping joined on February 5th. She is a warm-hearted, last year also signed up to participate in the Community Property Committee's preparatory group. But after a trip to Wuhan in mid-january, she returned to Shiyan and spent 20 days in self-imposed isolation before joining the volunteer team.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteers move residents'parcels into relief tents. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Just began to work, Bao Qinyong was assigned to the "persuasion post. ". The third day of the first lunar month is the second day of the Blue Mountain County closure, 6 am, Genius Light, Bao Qinyong got up to wash gargle. After breakfast, he thermometed himself as if he were fine, then left the house in a volunteer's red vest, mask and alcohol.

Community closed after the four gates closed three, only the middle of the gate pass, Baoqinyong and a few volunteers on guard here, in turn check the documents of the entry and exit personnel. Between 7:30 am and 8:30 am is the peak time for the "four categories of people" to go to work. People who need to go out to work are lined up in front of the only open gate with their names, ID numbers, contact details and work permits written on them. To prevent potential cross-contamination, people must be separated by two or three meters.

After the morning rush hour, "four kinds of personnel" can still go out, but the number of people is much less, the gate no longer need so many volunteers. Bao Qinyong began to patrol in the community, persuade those who roam outside the residents to go home.

Bao Qinyong said that at the beginning of a period of time, each household can go out every three days to buy food. Many old people do not want to obey the rules, just go out to buy cabbage, half an hour later want to go out to buy radish. Baoqinyong felt that they were so lonely. "I wanted to go out and talk to someone when my children were away, " he said. He would chat with the elderly people and teach them how to shop online.

He also counsels dog walkers and sunbathers to stay indoors, at least not in groups, to avoid cross-contamination. "Most people understand that, but they can't help but have a few troublemakers. "

The Guan Army has encountered uncooperative residents. Once he stood guard at the door, a young man did not wear a mask suddenly ran down from the upstairs, also kicked the door of the table, ready to rush out of the community. Guan Jun and volunteers reported to the police, the police came, the young man said he and his girlfriend quarreled, "the phone is not clear, to face the solution. ". Volunteers gave him a mask, for his psychological counseling for half a day, and finally persuaded him to go back.

Cross the river by feeling the stones

Blue Mountain County has had a flexible system of meetings since the volunteer team was formed. Every day after 4 or 5 pm delivery, everyone will gather in the small square to discuss the work of the day, who encountered what problems, we discuss solutions, everyone should speak. "sometimes they discuss it in wechat groups even when they are lying in bed at night, " Guan said.

Xiao Ankang is a veteran, engaged in fire work at the airport, in early February was divided into "sub-dishes Group" , experienced a stone crossing the river, constantly adjust the work program process.

On January 26th, after the district was closed, most residents bought food on a small APP called Wechat. Local e-commerce platform will order residents to order vegetables, fruits, daily necessities and other units to bag, label the order, and then delivered to the small square in the community, a day more than 300 bags. Residents will wait for a call from a volunteer before coming to pick up their food.

To prevent potential cross-contamination, the volunteers spent time searching through packages for each person. Yang Xu, a member of the food group, recalled that on the night of February 5, when the platform brought the vegetables in, it was dark, a light rain and a little cold. To avoid getting wet, four volunteers carried the packages to a makeshift tent. When someone comes to pick up the food, they have to use their mobile phones to clean and pick over the dishes one by one, which is very troublesome.

"another problem is that many people don't use their real names when placing orders, and the phone numbers on the order labels can only see the first three and the last four, " Xiao said, adding that there were often cases during that time when packages were not picked up for several days after they were placed, "We can't find anyone. "

To solve these problems, volunteers began to discuss solutions in Daily Square meetings or Wechat group meetings. For example, some people have suggested that e-commerce platforms should try not to deliver food in the evening so that residents can get food as soon as possible so that they can eat all kinds of food ordered on the same day, some people have asked to communicate with the e-commerce platform, let them provide complete information. After two or three conversations, the problem was really solved.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the closure, volunteers will place packages ordered from the Internet on trolleys and deliver them to the floor below. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Xiao Ankang has his own ideas, he hopes to improve the efficiency of the dishes, take dishes. He said he would "number" the hundreds of bags of vegetables that he would bring into the community each day, and arrange them in rows across the square in order of numbers. Volunteers would also tell residents their food numbers when they called or texted them.

"In that case, when you come to pick up your food, tell me you're number 100, and I'll be able to pick out your portion in a row after row, " Yang Xu said, residents are asked to check the information and take it away. "It will not be handed to them directly, there will be no direct contact. "

Sometimes, says Yang Xu, there's a sudden increase in the number of packages per day. When a volunteer holds a meeting, he suggests, "it would be a lot faster" to separate packages into piles on different platforms and then number them individually.

In addition to dividing dishes, other problems will be solved by a similar mechanism. "For example, statistical health information form, at the very beginning, everyone in the residents' wechat group replies in the form of a link. " Xiao Ankang said that there are more than 100 households in a residents' wechat group, and each household must reply "health, normal body temperature, " and so on, with a message card, and it's really fast. "Then someone offered to register with a wechat APP that filled out a questionnaire, and it worked out in no time. "

After the closure of the building to increase the task

As the outbreak of new crown pneumonia continues to change, control in Shiyan is getting stronger and stronger.

On the evening of February 12, the Zhangwan District command issued a "wartime control circular" , which read: "This is an extraordinary time, an extraordinary action, a necessity and a necessity, " said Xiao Xu, deputy district chief and deputy commander of the Zhangwan District military command, zhangwan District is not the worst affected area in Shiyan, and the move is intended to consolidate a phased effort to "prevent the formation of second-and third-generation infections" .

According to a previous report by the HSINKING newspaper, according to Lin Hongchao, director of the China University of Political Science and Law, only the National People's Congress and the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress can declare a state of war under the Constitution, wartime control measures can only be taken in a state of war, and Zhangwan District's so-called "wartime control" has no legal basis. "wartime" is not an accurate legal term, but an expression of the emergency management system, Wang Xixin, a professor at Peking University Law School, told the Beijing News.

For residents of Blue Mountains County, the doors of the 14 buildings in the complex were quickly locked after the "wartime blackout" began.

In recent days, the biggest problem for the Guan Army is opening doors for people to enter and exit buildings. January 26 after the closure of the community, "four categories of people" holding a pass can enter the community, the community has only one gate. But now the building is also closed, every day someone in front of each door, lock the door.

"for the 'four categories' , we would have required them to go from 7:30-8:00 in the morning to 6:00-6:30 in the evening, with volunteers on duty downstairs to confirm their passes. But in fact, everyone's travel time is not uniform, and the time for entering and leaving the building is not fixed,"Guan said, and the whole community building keys only a total of 4 sets, in order to strict, unified management, all placed in the property company security captain and several community personnel hands. "So every time someone comes in and out outside the allotted time, we have to run back and forth. "

On February 13, at five or six o'clock in the morning, Guan Jun's phone rang. Someone wanted to go to work. He got up and ran to open the door. During the 7-9 pm rush hour, he made at least 50 runs to each door and building. "I also ran, the head of security also ran, and we all ran separately. My legs hurt. "

The Guan Army is getting tired. On Feb. 14, he asked residents who needed to leave their homes if they could get temporary accommodation until the outbreak was over? "Of course, we're just making suggestions, " Guan said.

"Wartime Control" after the closure of the community, volunteers in the outdoor rest. Photo courtesy of the respondents

"wartime control announcement" before the release of that afternoon, Xiao Ankang from wechat group heard the wind. He just put forward the number of dishes not long program, all of a sudden invalidated. Because the closure of the building, the residents can no longer take food in the small square. The volunteers decided that food would be delivered downstairs from the 13th, and Yang Xu borrowed half a dozen trolleys from the supermarket.

In addition to open the door, food and other services, gas card recharge such daily chores have become impossible to complete.

A volunteer said that February 13, "closure" of the first day, many residents reported that the gas is running out, need to go to the bank recharge. In a wechat group discussing community work, a volunteer said the work should be handled by the property company, while the property said it should be handed over to the volunteer. The highest temperature in Shiyan that day was 19 degrees, and by afternoon, the volunteers who had been out for most of the day were almost sweating profusely. Yang Xu didn't want to see people passing the buck, so he decided to go to the bank and top up the money for the residents.

On the morning of Feb. 14, Yang Xu received gas cards from 120 residents from the volunteers in charge of each building, separated by building number, wrapped in paper and packed in a wine box. After waiting in line for two hours at the bank, he finally recharged all his gas cards. By the time he got home, it was 12:00, and he said on the Wechat Group, please understand, I'll call you later, please come back down and get it.

After 10 pm on February 15, the moon had already climbed into the branches, and Bao Qinyong finally finished his day's volunteer work and went home. Standing at the door, he sprayed his coat with rubbing alcohol and took his temperature with a thermometer before he stepped inside.

In Bao Qinyong's view, since he became a volunteer, the time of each day passed in a flash, "To be honest, you can't really say what you do every day. It's not helping [ others ] , it's all in your own neighborhood. As long as your neighborhood is built, isn't your life better? "

(Guan Jun and Yu Ping are pseudonyms)
